The paper deals with the construction of graph spanners, which is a topic in both theoretical computer science and computational geometry. The use of distance oracles and graph algorithms suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category. The focus on geometric graphs and stretch factor suggests that cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a likely category. The use of randomized algorithms and analysis of their performance suggests that cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category. The use of graph theory and combinatorial optimization suggests that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) are also possible categories.
